Introduction¶

In this project we will investigate a dataset that gatheres information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil. The dataset contains information about each appointment such as: gender, age, date of scheduling, date of actual appointment, neighborhood, wheather the pateints are holding scholarship or not , sms-reminder as well as wheather the pateint suffer from one or more disease. our analysis will focus on the different factors that may affect the show-up of pateints to their appointment.

Questions to explore during this project:2

  1. Do factors such as receiving SMS, Age, Gender, Scholarship affect pateints showing up to their appointments?
  2. what is the show up ratio and the time span between scheduling the appointment and the appointment day and how the showing up percentage is affected by the waiting days?
  3. Which Neighbourhoods are associated with the highst no. of show up pateints?
  4. Does the pateint suffering from a disease affect his/her showing up?

  1. changing datatype of some columns to appropriate datatype so that we can easily extract date and analyze it.
  2. change the column name and correct the typos to more readable way and better in column calling
  3. correcting the wrong age values (age<0)

In [12]:
#generating a function for chart labelling of x and y axis and stating the title
def chart_label(x_label,y_label,Title):
    plt.xlabel(x_label,  fontsize='xx-large')
    plt.ylabel(y_label, fontsize='xx-large')
    plt.title(Title, fontsize='xx-large');
    return plt.show()

Conclusions¶

After analyzing the data we concluded that:¶
  1. sending sms is not neccessary to ensure the show up of the pateint. 56.6% did not receive the sms and still go to the appointment while 23.3% receive sms and went to the appointment.
  2. age may be a relevent factor where the mean age of pateints who showed up were around 37 while pateint who did not show up were around 34.
  3. gender showed no effect on showing up to appointments were equal male and female showing up percentage were detected.
  4. the majority of pateints who have scholarship do not show up to appointments while most of pateints who do not have scholarships show up to their appointments.
  5. the majority of pateints (~80%) who schedueled their appointments attend it.
  6. pateints tends to show up when the time span between scheduling the appointment and the actual appointment date is less than or equal to 10 days(the attendance percentage = 85.5 %) while when the waiting days are more than 10 days the show up percentage droped down to 67.5%.
  7. in this study, 81 neighbourhoods were included, one of them "ILHAS OCENICAS DE TRINDADE" no pateint attend their appointment may be due to lack of transportation or bad weather. while "JARDIM CAMBURI" neighbourhood has the heighest scheduled appointments and highest show up rate as may be this hospital is in the center of the city.
  8. it seems that the pateint suffering from a certein disease either hypertension, diabetes or alcoholism doesn't greatly affect the pateint showing up.

to summer it up, in our openion, the most affecting factors are Neighbourhood and the awaiting time between scheduling the appointment and actual appointment date.

Limitations¶

  1. The collected dataset investigated in this analysis was over a short period time and require more clarification regarding geografical data, weather condition so that the Data would provide more insight into other factors affecting the show up rates.
  2. More data collection and analysis are required for the health status regarding each pateint and how it could affect his/her showing up to appointment.
